==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Evidentiary
<hw>Ev`i*den"ti*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Furnishing
evidence; asserting; proving; evidential.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When a fact is supposed, although incorrectly, to be
<qex>evidentiary</qex> of, or a mark of, some other fact.</q>
<rj><qau>J. S. Mill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evidently</ent>⟦br⟧
